            "text": "ROOT",
            "relation": "null"
        },
        {
            "id": 1,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "Update summarization is a form of multi-document summarization \r",
            "relation": "BACKGROUND"
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "where a document set must be summarized in the context of other documents \r",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 3,
            "parent": 2,
            "text": "assumed to be known . <S>\r",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 4,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "Efficient update summarization must focus on identifying new information and avoiding repetition of known information . <S>\r",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 5,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "In Query-focused summarization , the task is to produce a summary as an answer to a given query . <S>\r",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 6,
            "parent": 0,
            "text": "We introduce a new task , Query-Chain Summarization , \r",
            "relation": "ROOT"
        },
        {
            "id": 7,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "which combines aspects of the two previous tasks : \r",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 8,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "starting from a given document set , \r",
            "relation": "EXEMPLIFICATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 9,
            "parent": 8,
            "text": "increasingly specific queries are considered , \r",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 10,
            "parent": 8,
            "text": "and a new summary is produced at each step . <S>\r",
            "relation": "JOINT"
        },
        {
            "id": 11,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "This process models exploratory search : \r",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 12,
            "parent": 11,
            "text": "a user explores a new topic \r",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 13,
            "parent": 12,
            "text": "by submitting a sequence of queries , \r",
            "relation": "MANNER-MEANS"
        },
        {
            "id": 14,
            "parent": 13,
            "text": "inspecting a summary of the result set \r",
            "relation": "JOINT"
        },
        {
            "id": 15,
            "parent": 14,
            "text": "and phrasing a new query at each step . <S>\r",
            "relation": "JOINT"
        },
        {
            "id": 16,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "We present a novel dataset \r",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 17,
            "parent": 16,
            "text": "comprising 22 query-chains sessions of length up to 3 with 3 matching human summaries each in the consumer-health domain . <S>\r",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 18,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "Our analysis demonstrates \r",
            "relation": "EVALUATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 19,
            "parent": 18,
            "text": "that summaries produced in the context of such exploratory process are different from informative summaries . <S>\r",
            "relation": "ATTRIBUTION"
        },
        {
            "id": 20,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "We present an algorithm for Query-Chain Summarization \r",
            "relation": "EVALUATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 21,
            "parent": 20,
            "text": "based on a new LDA topic model variant . <S>\r",
            "relation": "BACKGROUND"
        },
        {
            "id": 22,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "Evaluation indicates \r",
            "relation": "EVALUATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 23,
            "parent": 22,
            "text": "the algorithm improves on strong baselines . <S>\r",
            "relation": "ATTRIBUTION"
        }
    ]
}